# Step-5 Itinerary Split Leaves Only An Early Admission Filter And No Honest Late Gate

Status: `INFERRED` from a `VERIFIED` Step-4 dossier and Step-5 split audit

`Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` does not survive the authorized Step-5 repair
pass on the frozen exact packet ledger.

The early split,
`pre-trigger delay filter`,
is honest on the inherited window, thresholds, sign sheet, and spectator
screen.
On the recorded dossier it still separates hostile `F_DT(delta, eta)` from
friendly `F_SS(mu)` and `F_SL(rho)`.
But its downstream gate
`G_pre(P_n; I) = (t_clk, t_trig, max_[0,t_trig] D_off / D_on; sign sheet)`
remains only a narrow admission filter and does not add a new theorem-facing
or counterexample-facing quantity beyond the stronger template-defect and
leakage gates.

The late split,
`next-stage transfer-start filter`,
is not an honest repair.
If it keeps the original late threshold clause `|E_n(t_next)| >= theta_E`,
the same `F_SL(rho)` ambiguity remains because the local record still does not
uniformly fix the exact `t_next` trace.
If it weakens that clause to earlier transfer onset or merely positive
`Q_next`, it changes the frozen late event language after outcomes are known.

The earned Step-5 verdict is therefore negative:
the itinerary route should be discarded,
with the decisive bottleneck recorded as late-stage event-trace rigidity
rather than spectator leakage.

