+# Template-Defect Near-Closure Step-6 Next Test Is The Carried `F_SL(rho)` Family On The Repaired Defect Sheet
+
+Status: `INFERRED` Step-6 next-test assignment from the repaired ledger
+
+On the frozen canonical packet sheet, the first honest next theorem question
+for `Template-Defect Near-Closure` is whether the carried scale-separated
+friendly family `F_SL(rho)`, restricted to `0 < rho <= 1/16`, stays inside
+the repaired defect gate
+`G_tmpl(P_n; I) = (Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)`
+with
+`Delta_tmpl <= 1/4`
+and
+`Delta_spec <= 49/256`
+uniformly on the fixed window `I = [0, 1]`, while hostile `F_DT(delta, eta)`
+remains excluded on that same observable.
+
+This is the smallest meaningful carried-forward test family because
+`F_SL(1/16)` is the recorded boundary witness on both repaired defect
+coordinates.
+So the next phase should try to lift that boundary witness into a one-
+parameter friendly theorem on the same frozen ledger, rather than treat the
+calibration dossier as theorem completion.
+
+Before any honest theorem or counterexample claim, the local record still
+needs one explicit `rho`-dependent formula ledger for
+`Delta_tmpl`
+and
+`Delta_spec`,
+one proof that the friendly worst case is really the boundary point
+`rho = 1/16` or one corrected extremal parameter on the same family,
+one explicit hostile-side quantitative gap for
+`Delta_tmpl`
+if a full family-separation theorem is wanted,
+and one statement of whether the result stops at family-level admissibility or
+feeds a later same-currency transfer lemma.
+
+The strongest claim currently supported is narrower:
+the repaired object gives a theorem-facing insertion line that one explicit
+friendly scale-separated family may remain inside the repaired defect sheet on
+the frozen ledger while the hostile comparator fails on that same observable.
+It does not yet justify any theorem that small
+`(Delta_tmpl, Delta_spec)`
+forces the leakage sheet, forces the Tao itinerary, or proves near-circuit
+behavior beyond the audited packet class and carried family.
+
+Filed from:
